1
00:00:06,339 --> 00:00:08,758
<i>This man, who's glaring at Mapo Tofu,</i>

2
00:00:09,342 --> 00:00:10,552
<i>is Takuzo Mitsuda.</i>

3
00:00:10,635 --> 00:00:11,886
TAKUZO MITSUDA
FIRST-CLASS ARCHITECT/SINGLE

4
00:00:11,970 --> 00:00:14,055
<i>He is a protagonist of this story.</i>

5
00:00:17,434 --> 00:00:19,269
<i>They didn't order any </i>gyoza<i>,</i>

6
00:00:19,352 --> 00:00:22,564
<i>and his other favorite dish</i>
<i>is getting cold.</i>

7
00:00:23,106 --> 00:00:24,566
<i>But there's a bigger problem.</i>

8
00:00:25,108 --> 00:00:26,818
You love Chinese food, right?

9
00:00:26,901 --> 00:00:29,696
But we can't order this much
if there's only two people.

10
00:00:29,779 --> 00:00:32,615
If three of us get married,
it's three times the fun.

11
00:00:32,699 --> 00:00:35,577
But we only carry a third
of the responsibilities and burdens.

12
00:00:35,660 --> 00:00:36,870
Isn't that great?

13
00:00:37,454 --> 00:00:39,205
<i>It's this conversation.</i>

14
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:42,333
How about having a trial?

15
00:00:42,917 --> 00:00:43,835
What do you think?

16
00:00:46,671 --> 00:00:47,714
Is this some kind of

17
00:00:48,965 --> 00:00:50,467
suspicious solicitation?

18
00:00:51,426 --> 00:00:53,762
No, I'm being serious.

19
00:00:53,845 --> 00:00:56,890
If that's true, then this is just crazy.

20
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:01,895
Isn't it an awesome idea?

21
00:01:02,687 --> 00:01:03,730
Are you serious too?

22
00:01:04,314 --> 00:01:05,190
Huh? Um...

23
00:01:05,815 --> 00:01:10,111
Well, if Shinpei wants to, why not?

24
00:01:11,237 --> 00:01:12,947
But why me?

25
00:01:13,573 --> 00:01:17,160
That's because we both like you.

26
00:01:17,243 --> 00:01:18,495
- Right?
- What?

27
00:01:19,579 --> 00:01:22,248
W-Well... maybe? Oh!

28
00:01:23,166 --> 00:01:25,251
You seemed lonely by yourself.

29
00:01:29,839 --> 00:01:31,925
Oh, I see.

30
00:01:34,135 --> 00:01:35,595
So, basically

31
00:01:36,805 --> 00:01:40,975
this crazy idea is his way of telling you
he doesn't want to get married.

32
00:01:41,059 --> 00:01:44,521
You don't want to admit that,
so you're going along with it.

33
00:01:44,604 --> 00:01:47,690
And conveniently decided to use me.
I get it now.

34
00:01:47,774 --> 00:01:49,609
You've got it all wrong, Takuzo.

35
00:01:49,692 --> 00:01:51,111
Take my advice,

36
00:01:51,194 --> 00:01:52,946
wake up and face the reality.

37
00:01:53,988 --> 00:01:55,031
You know,

38
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:57,784
we're both
at the age to take life seriously.

39
00:01:59,327 --> 00:02:02,789
Shut up. It's none of your business.

40
00:02:03,456 --> 00:02:05,250
You dragged me into this.

41
00:02:05,333 --> 00:02:07,877
What's the problem anyway?
Just go along with it!

42
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:11,047
You'll never be able to get married
any other way!

43
00:02:11,131 --> 00:02:11,965
What?

44
00:02:12,048 --> 00:02:13,258
Mia, relax.

45
00:02:13,341 --> 00:02:14,175
But...

46
00:02:14,259 --> 00:02:16,511
Hey. Let me make this clear.

47
00:02:18,221 --> 00:02:22,308
I'd rather be alone
than to get married this way.

48
00:02:29,107 --> 00:02:30,108
He left.

49
00:02:31,484 --> 00:02:36,364
<i>This is a story of these three,</i>
<i>who had a bad start, and their marriage.</i>

50
00:02:37,365 --> 00:02:38,783
What's their problem?

51
00:02:42,287 --> 00:02:43,872
<i>Two husbands, one wife.</i>

52
00:02:50,461 --> 00:02:52,755
BEAVER ARCHITECTS

53
00:02:53,798 --> 00:02:55,884
- Hi.
- Good morning.

54
00:02:59,554 --> 00:03:01,389
<i>Since then, he's been irritated.</i>

55
00:03:04,142 --> 00:03:05,518
Oh, come on.

56
00:03:06,477 --> 00:03:09,063
Sorry, Manager. I broke it again.

57
00:03:09,981 --> 00:03:11,858
Times sure have changed.

58
00:03:12,442 --> 00:03:15,028
<i>Very very irritated.</i>

59
00:03:15,528 --> 00:03:17,280
- Excuse me.
- Oh, Ms. Tenma.

60
00:03:17,363 --> 00:03:19,532
This is our next client's information.

61
00:03:20,325 --> 00:03:21,576
CLIENT: FAMILY OF THREE

62
00:03:23,661 --> 00:03:24,495
Thanks.

63
00:03:28,082 --> 00:03:28,917
Takuzo.

64
00:03:29,792 --> 00:03:32,837
Do you want to do it after work today?

65
00:03:35,548 --> 00:03:36,591
Sounds good.

66
00:03:37,258 --> 00:03:39,636
<i>A chance to blow off steam.</i>

67
00:03:44,390 --> 00:03:46,351
BEAVER ARCHITECTS

68
00:03:54,859 --> 00:03:58,696
<i>This person working on a task</i>
<i>which is almost as delicate as a rabbit,</i>

69
00:03:58,780 --> 00:03:59,864
<i>is Sayo Tenma.</i>

70
00:03:59,948 --> 00:04:01,824
SAYO TENMA
SECOND-CLASS ARCHITECT/SINGLE

71
00:04:02,575 --> 00:04:04,327
<i>She's Takuzo's junior co-worker</i>

72
00:04:04,410 --> 00:04:07,914
<i>and his building block buddy.</i>
<i>They made a large-scale piece together.</i>

73
00:04:09,290 --> 00:04:12,752
<i>By the way, she believes in</i>
<i>friendship between men and women.</i>

74
00:04:17,006 --> 00:04:18,841
Oh, you saw Mia?

75
00:04:19,509 --> 00:04:22,303
Yeah. I invited her to Pakkun's funeral.

76
00:04:23,888 --> 00:04:25,181
Is she doing well?

77
00:04:25,265 --> 00:04:26,432
Yup.

78
00:04:27,141 --> 00:04:28,393
She's well, but...

79
00:04:29,310 --> 00:04:30,144
But?

80
00:04:30,979 --> 00:04:33,356
She was selfish as usual.

81
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:37,610
She brought her new boyfriend with her
to make me jealous.

82
00:04:38,361 --> 00:04:39,570
So much drama.

83
00:04:39,654 --> 00:04:41,114
On top of all that,

84
00:04:41,197 --> 00:04:44,575
she yelled at me
saying I'll never be able to get married.

85
00:04:45,827 --> 00:04:50,123
No one in the world is as selfish as her.

86
00:04:51,124 --> 00:04:54,961
She's a human faulty housing
born with a construction defect.

87
00:04:55,545 --> 00:04:56,796
You sound pretty pissed.

88
00:04:56,879 --> 00:04:58,423
That's because I am.

89
00:05:01,634 --> 00:05:03,803
But you still like her, huh?

90
00:05:05,430 --> 00:05:06,264
What?

91
00:05:07,515 --> 00:05:08,725
Were you listening?

92
00:05:10,101 --> 00:05:13,771
You get worked up about things you like

93
00:05:13,855 --> 00:05:17,025
but you pay no attention
to things you're not interested in.

94
00:05:17,692 --> 00:05:18,818
I'm the same.

95
00:05:20,778 --> 00:05:22,488
That doesn't mean...

96
00:05:23,823 --> 00:05:27,577
<i>In the end,</i>
<i>his irritation turned into confusion.</i>

97
00:05:29,287 --> 00:05:32,999
TAKUZO? SHINPEI, ME

98
00:05:34,876 --> 00:05:35,710
I'm home.

99
00:05:36,335 --> 00:05:37,545
Welcome home.

100
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:45,178
TAKUZO? SHINPEI, ME

101
00:05:49,599 --> 00:05:51,476
Are you okay with how things went?

102
00:05:52,685 --> 00:05:53,519
Huh?

103
00:05:54,437 --> 00:05:55,438
About Takuzo.

104
00:05:56,397 --> 00:06:00,359
I know he declined, but wasn't there
something more you wanted to tell him?

105
00:06:11,829 --> 00:06:13,414
MIA

106
00:06:13,498 --> 00:06:19,670
I'M SORRY ABOUT THE OTHER DAY.
CAN YOU MAKE TIME TO TALK AGAIN?

107
00:06:23,091 --> 00:06:25,426
You'll never be able to get married!

108
00:06:25,510 --> 00:06:27,720
You still like her, huh?

109
00:06:40,608 --> 00:06:42,652
I've made my decision, Pakkun.

110
00:06:43,486 --> 00:06:45,363
<i>Huh? About what?</i>

111
00:06:53,454 --> 00:06:55,498
MATCHMAKING PARTY

112
00:06:57,416 --> 00:06:59,544
REGISTER HERE!

113
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:04,757
I'll do it.

114
00:07:05,341 --> 00:07:06,676
<i>I didn't see that coming.</i>

115
00:07:09,011 --> 00:07:10,596
MATCHMAKING PARTY
REGISTRATION FORM

116
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:11,556
<i>Okay.</i>

117
00:07:12,056 --> 00:07:13,099
<i>Good luck.</i>

118
00:07:18,563 --> 00:07:21,315
I'M SORRY ABOUT THE OTHER DAY.
CAN YOU MAKE TIME TO TALK AGAIN?

119
00:07:23,067 --> 00:07:25,611
Reply already.

120
00:07:27,947 --> 00:07:30,283
TAKUZO

121
00:07:32,034 --> 00:07:32,869
<i>And,</i>

122
00:07:33,703 --> 00:07:35,705
<i>it's the day of the matchmaking party.</i>

123
00:07:40,126 --> 00:07:42,253
<i>Takuzo didn't get a wink of sleep.</i>

124
00:07:43,171 --> 00:07:45,089
<i>His eyes are as red as rabbits' eyes.</i>

125
00:07:46,215 --> 00:07:47,884
MATCHMAKING PARTY
HAVE FUN!

126
00:07:48,551 --> 00:07:52,388
Hello everyone.
Thank you for your patience!

127
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:58,186
Let the matchmaking party begin!

128
00:07:58,269 --> 00:08:00,688
Ladies, please take a seat.

129
00:08:01,731 --> 00:08:04,192
- First, introduce yourselves!
- I can do this.

130
00:08:11,365 --> 00:08:12,241
Hello.

131
00:08:12,825 --> 00:08:14,202
I'm Takuzo Mitsuda.

132
00:08:14,702 --> 00:08:15,536
Thank you.

133
00:08:15,620 --> 00:08:16,662
PROFILE CARD

134
00:08:17,371 --> 00:08:18,706
I'm Kana Ohno.

135
00:08:19,957 --> 00:08:20,791
Um.

136
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:21,792
Yes?

137
00:08:22,710 --> 00:08:25,755
Once you're married,
what kind of family do you want to build?

138
00:08:27,590 --> 00:08:29,842
Oh, you don't waste time, do you?

139
00:08:30,635 --> 00:08:32,303
You're an architect?

140
00:08:32,386 --> 00:08:33,471
Yes.

141
00:08:33,554 --> 00:08:34,680
Wow.

142
00:08:35,681 --> 00:08:38,184
Why did you become an architect?

143
00:08:38,267 --> 00:08:39,101
Huh?

144
00:08:40,186 --> 00:08:42,647
Why did I... become one?

145
00:08:45,107 --> 00:08:46,400
One moment please.

146
00:08:49,487 --> 00:08:51,447
I like building things.

147
00:08:52,073 --> 00:08:54,200
No, then I could've chosen carpenter.

148
00:08:55,451 --> 00:08:57,745
Building blocks. My hobby became my job?

149
00:09:00,831 --> 00:09:03,000
Time to promote yourselves!

150
00:09:07,004 --> 00:09:12,635
Building blocks are known to be
the best educational toys for children.

151
00:09:12,718 --> 00:09:15,805
But the best part is that
you can create anything you imagine

152
00:09:15,888 --> 00:09:18,391
such as buildings or huge robots,

153
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:22,728
a whole city, or a monster.

154
00:09:22,812 --> 00:09:27,400
You can make whatever you want
through trial and error.

155
00:09:28,192 --> 00:09:30,570
It took me three months to make this.

156
00:09:31,279 --> 00:09:35,032
It felt as if something hidden in
my subconscious mind had been discovered.

157
00:09:35,116 --> 00:09:37,785
Like I've met
a version of myself I never knew before.

158
00:09:37,868 --> 00:09:41,831
That is truly... an amazing thing.

159
00:09:47,211 --> 00:09:48,838
You might think that

160
00:09:49,672 --> 00:09:51,424
building blocks are just toys--

161
00:09:51,507 --> 00:09:52,341
Hey,

162
00:09:52,842 --> 00:09:56,971
you should talk about yourself
rather than building blocks.

163
00:10:03,185 --> 00:10:05,730
The weather is great today.

164
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:08,399
Yes, it is.

165
00:10:09,734 --> 00:10:10,568
Bye.

166
00:10:23,497 --> 00:10:25,875
SHINPEI DANCE

167
00:10:25,958 --> 00:10:28,252
DM ME FOR WORK

168
00:10:28,336 --> 00:10:32,923
SO COOL
YOUR LAST SHOW WAS AWESOME!

169
