BREAKING NEWS: AN UNIDENTIFIED BODY
FOUND IN KAMIOKA CITY, NIIGATA

170
00:10:42,975 --> 00:10:45,311
THE POLICE ARE INVESTIGATING

171
00:11:03,329 --> 00:11:04,914
MATCHMAKING PARTY
HAVE FUN!

172
00:11:09,418 --> 00:11:13,798
<i>He paid a fee of 8,000 yen to get nothing</i>
<i>but a sense of loneliness and inferiority.</i>

173
00:11:14,340 --> 00:11:17,176
<i>They threw in emptiness and defeat</i>
<i>as a bonus too.</i>

174
00:11:19,178 --> 00:11:23,224
<i>His ex-girlfriends' words</i>
<i>flashed through his mind.</i>

175
00:11:25,309 --> 00:11:28,020
Takuzo, you're so boring.

176
00:11:28,104 --> 00:11:30,106
He was annoying.

177
00:11:30,189 --> 00:11:31,148
Boring.

178
00:11:31,232 --> 00:11:32,900
Annoying.

179
00:11:34,318 --> 00:11:36,612
<i>He has two ex-girlfriends. That's it.</i>

180
00:11:37,863 --> 00:11:38,697
Takuzo!

181
00:11:47,415 --> 00:11:51,085
You didn't return my messages
or calls, so...

182
00:11:56,215 --> 00:11:57,800
Can we talk for a bit?

183
00:11:59,635 --> 00:12:01,595
Hey, you look pale.

184
00:12:01,679 --> 00:12:03,973
Huh? Hey, Takuzo?

185
00:12:04,473 --> 00:12:06,517
Takuzo!

186
00:12:07,268 --> 00:12:09,437
Takuzo, come on.

187
00:12:19,155 --> 00:12:21,407
Thirty-six point four? Totally average!

188
00:12:21,490 --> 00:12:22,491
Sorry.

189
00:12:23,451 --> 00:12:26,495
I'm relieved you're not ill or anything.

190
00:12:26,579 --> 00:12:31,000
But you went there on an empty stomach
and no sleep? How nervous were you?

191
00:12:31,083 --> 00:12:32,084
Sorry.

192
00:12:32,918 --> 00:12:36,172
I asked Shinpei to go grocery shopping
to cook for you, okay?

193
00:12:36,964 --> 00:12:37,965
Sorry.

194
00:12:38,048 --> 00:12:39,758
Don't apologize so much.

195
00:12:41,385 --> 00:12:42,303
I'm sorry.

196
00:12:42,386 --> 00:12:43,721
Stop it.

197
00:12:43,804 --> 00:12:44,722
I think

198
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:47,224
you were right.

199
00:12:50,561 --> 00:12:51,604
It seems

200
00:12:52,897 --> 00:12:54,356
I really can't get married.

201
00:12:57,151 --> 00:12:57,985
I'm sorry.

202
00:12:58,569 --> 00:13:00,946
I went too far that day.

203
00:13:03,574 --> 00:13:05,159
When I was in grade school,

204
00:13:06,368 --> 00:13:09,163
there was a boy called Hiro in my class.

205
00:13:10,581 --> 00:13:14,502
I thought he was my best friend,
so I was always with him.

206
00:13:18,756 --> 00:13:19,924
But one day,

207
00:13:20,674 --> 00:13:21,926
my parents said...

208
00:13:24,512 --> 00:13:27,848
"Don't follow Hiro around so much."

209
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:34,813
Apparently, his parents
called the school about it.

210
00:13:36,524 --> 00:13:37,942
That I was bothering him.

211
00:13:43,364 --> 00:13:44,865
I'm just not good at it.

212
00:13:46,575 --> 00:13:49,745
Like how to read
people and relationships,

213
00:13:50,621 --> 00:13:53,541
or understand boundaries
and everything like that.

214
00:13:58,170 --> 00:13:59,672
It's the same with Pakkun.

215
00:14:00,714 --> 00:14:04,552
I didn't think
I'd love or miss them so much.

216
00:14:11,934 --> 00:14:13,352
Actually,

217
00:14:15,145 --> 00:14:17,106
I think you were right about me.

218
00:14:22,444 --> 00:14:24,321
I think I used you

219
00:14:25,948 --> 00:14:28,117
because I wanted to marry Shinpei.

220
00:14:31,036 --> 00:14:31,912
But,

221
00:14:33,372 --> 00:14:36,750
it's also true
that I thought it might work

222
00:14:38,002 --> 00:14:39,295
if it's the three of us.

223
00:14:41,964 --> 00:14:43,132
How should I put it?

224
00:14:43,966 --> 00:14:46,969
There were things
that were too much for me alone,

225
00:14:48,012 --> 00:14:51,891
but I think I can handle it if
there's another person to share it with.

226
00:14:53,767 --> 00:14:55,519
The distance we couldn't fill

227
00:14:56,186 --> 00:14:58,439
could be bridged by someone else,

228
00:14:58,522 --> 00:15:00,649
if another person stepped in...

229
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:02,484
Takuzo, are you okay?

230
00:15:02,568 --> 00:15:03,903
Oh, yeah.

231
00:15:03,986 --> 00:15:05,195
Do you have a fever?

232
00:15:05,279 --> 00:15:06,572
It was 36.4 degrees.

233
00:15:06,655 --> 00:15:09,241
What? Is your
normal temperature like, 34.2 degrees?

234
00:15:09,325 --> 00:15:11,160
- No.
- Of course not!

235
00:15:11,243 --> 00:15:12,745
What are those flowers for?

236
00:15:12,828 --> 00:15:15,164
I bought it. A get-well-soon gift.

237
00:15:15,247 --> 00:15:17,249
It says <i>Bukka</i>.

238
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,209
What's that?

239
00:15:19,293 --> 00:15:21,921
These are flowers you offer at funerals.

240
00:15:22,004 --> 00:15:23,505
There's flowers for that?

241
00:15:23,589 --> 00:15:25,674
Geez, talk about back luck.

242
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:28,177
Go and make some udon noodles.

243
00:15:29,011 --> 00:15:30,179
Open.

244
00:15:31,388 --> 00:15:33,390
Ta-da. Looks good.

245
00:15:34,683 --> 00:15:35,976
Thank you for the meal.

246
00:15:48,781 --> 00:15:49,615
How is it?

247
00:15:51,283 --> 00:15:52,368
It's really good.

248
00:15:52,451 --> 00:15:54,036
Thank goodness.

249
00:15:54,119 --> 00:15:56,080
You should eat while it's hot too, Mia.

250
00:15:56,163 --> 00:15:56,997
Yeah.

251
00:15:57,623 --> 00:15:58,999
- There.
- There.

252
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:00,918
And mine, too.

253
00:16:04,004 --> 00:16:05,589
- Sorry.
- Thanks.

254
00:16:10,344 --> 00:16:11,720
- I'll serve.
- Thanks.

255
00:16:13,931 --> 00:16:16,350
Wow, it looks so yummy.

256
00:16:16,934 --> 00:16:17,935
Nice.

257
00:16:18,852 --> 00:16:20,437
<i>Right now, Takuzo is thinking...</i>

258
00:16:20,521 --> 00:16:22,481
I haven't had your <i>udon</i> in a while.

259
00:16:22,564 --> 00:16:23,440
You're right.

260
00:16:23,524 --> 00:16:26,151
<i>"Having them take care of me</i>
<i>when I'm unwell</i>

261
00:16:26,235 --> 00:16:29,488
<i>makes me think</i>
<i>it's nice to have someone around.</i>

262
00:16:30,864 --> 00:16:32,574
<i>I'm so predictable."</i>

263
00:16:34,660 --> 00:16:37,746
Ready? Rock, paper, scissors.

264
00:16:38,247 --> 00:16:40,749
- Aw, why me?
- Yes!

265
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:42,793
Fine, I'll do it.

266
00:16:42,876 --> 00:16:43,794
Thank you.

267
00:16:43,877 --> 00:16:45,879
Sure, no problem.

268
00:16:45,963 --> 00:16:47,089
You need help?

269
00:16:47,172 --> 00:16:48,632
- No, it's fine.
- Really?

270
00:16:48,716 --> 00:16:49,925
Leave it to me.

271
00:16:50,009 --> 00:16:51,176
- Thanks.
- Sure.

272
00:17:09,862 --> 00:17:11,196
You feel better?

273
00:17:12,573 --> 00:17:13,407
Yeah.

274
00:17:14,158 --> 00:17:14,992
Thanks.

275
00:17:15,784 --> 00:17:16,618
Good.

276
00:17:20,664 --> 00:17:21,665
Shinpei.

277
00:17:24,418 --> 00:17:25,335
I think

278
00:17:26,712 --> 00:17:28,839
she really wants to marry you.

279
00:17:31,759 --> 00:17:33,510
This might be weird coming from me.

280
00:17:36,096 --> 00:17:38,015
But I really want you to consider it.

281
00:17:50,903 --> 00:17:53,030
I have. And that's my answer.

282
00:17:55,074 --> 00:17:57,326
I'm... scared.

283
00:17:59,536 --> 00:18:00,954
Of married life,

284
00:18:02,372 --> 00:18:04,500
and of parenting, if we have a child.

285
00:18:06,502 --> 00:18:08,754
I don't think the two of us can handle it.

286
00:18:11,298 --> 00:18:12,674
I'm not reliable

287
00:18:13,425 --> 00:18:16,011
and Mia isn't great
with responsibilities either.

288
00:18:19,973 --> 00:18:22,226
If we have someone like you by our side,

289
00:18:23,352 --> 00:18:25,062
it'll be super reassuring.

290
00:18:26,688 --> 00:18:28,273
Someone like me?

291
00:18:34,321 --> 00:18:35,489
You're responsible

292
00:18:36,448 --> 00:18:38,117
and full of kindness.

293
00:18:40,577 --> 00:18:42,579
Plus, you're just fun to be with.

294
00:18:55,175 --> 00:18:57,010
Let me think about it.

295
00:18:58,512 --> 00:18:59,346
What?

296
00:19:01,807 --> 00:19:03,016
Give me six months.

297
00:19:04,893 --> 00:19:06,186
No. Let's see.

298
00:19:07,062 --> 00:19:08,647
I need at least a year.

299
00:19:10,274 --> 00:19:11,775
Y-You mean

300
00:19:13,569 --> 00:19:16,196
you'll try it out for a year?

301
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:18,615
- What?
- Thank you, Takuzo!

302
00:19:18,699 --> 00:19:19,825
No, no. Hey.

303
00:19:19,908 --> 00:19:20,868
Wait. Hey!

304
00:19:20,951 --> 00:19:21,827
Mia!

305
00:19:21,910 --> 00:19:23,495
- Mia.
- No, wait!

306
00:19:23,579 --> 00:19:25,205
He said he'll give it a try.

307
00:19:25,289 --> 00:19:28,041
- What? Really?
- Yay! Hooray!

308
00:19:28,125 --> 00:19:29,334
No, that's not it!

309
00:19:29,418 --> 00:19:32,629
- Hooray!
- Hooray!

310
00:19:32,713 --> 00:19:34,006
- What's this?
- Happy dance.

311
00:19:34,089 --> 00:19:35,090
No way.

312
00:19:36,049 --> 00:19:37,843
- Happy dance?
- Happy dance.

313
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:40,345
A three-person marriage?

314
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:46,560
This is too much twirling.

315
00:19:50,105 --> 00:19:52,733
Th-Then, um... Go to a hot spring.

316
00:19:52,816 --> 00:19:54,067
A hot spring?

317
00:19:54,151 --> 00:19:55,527
<i>The three of us.</i>

318
00:19:55,611 --> 00:19:57,154
In the end, I got dumped.

319
00:19:57,738 --> 00:19:59,364
<i>You're the one she chose.</i>

320
00:19:59,448 --> 00:20:01,158
- That really is creepy.
- What?

321
00:20:01,658 --> 00:20:04,119
- They're so fluffy.
- So fluffy.

322
00:20:04,203 --> 00:20:05,495
